<task id="064" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-17 — Summarization compression service (sliding window; LLM summary for oldest M turns)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Cross-Conversation Memory (Pillar 7)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (parallel after 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>053 (workspace state wired)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, services, memory</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New service in AI services tree; LLM-backed; consumed by memory composition + chat prompt assembly; budget interaction critical.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build summarization compression service that compresses the oldest M turns when the
    chat conversation history exceeds a configured sliding-window budget. Place in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/`. Public API:
    `Task&lt;string&gt; CompressTurnsAsync(IEnumerable&lt;ChatTurn&gt; turns, CancellationToken ct)`
    which returns an LLM-generated `[Conversation summary: ...]` block. Persists the
    summary as a memory entry in Cosmos `sessions` container so subsequent turns reuse
    rather than re-summarize. Uses the GPT-4o-mini deployment (cheap path) per
    `chat-architecture.md`. Respects the 8K system prompt budget per NFR-10 — the
    summary itself is budget-aware (caps at ~500 tokens). Wire into the existing
    `PlaybookChatContextProvider` lifecycle without modifying its public signature.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer with familiarity with Cosmos `sessions` container +
    GPT-4o-mini cost-tier patterns + `PlaybookChatContextProvider`.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Service implemented + registered; compresses oldest M turns into a summary block;
    persists summary to Cosmos; reuses on subsequent invocations; budget caps respected.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
